  "name": "Copper Coral",
  "mood": "Aether",
  "engines": [
    "Obrix"
  ],
  "description": "Dual Bandpass architecture: proc1=BP at 340 Hz (chest resonance, vowel 'UH') and proc2=BP at 2400 Hz (throat resonance, vowel 'EE'). Two resonance peaks separated by 2 octaves create a formant pair — the coral's voice has two chambers. Square + Triangle sources give the signal harmonic content for both filters to carve. The copper tint comes from fmDepth 0.32: enough cross-modulation to add metallic shimmer without destroying the formant clarity. Coprime LFOs breathe each filter independently.",
